This event handler calls this.props.onClick(). The Square’s onClick prop was specified by the Board.
3. Since the Board passed onClick={() => this.handleClick(i)} to Square, the Square calls the Board’s handleClick(i) when clicked.
4. We have not defined the handleClick() method yet, so our code crashes. If you click a square now, you should see a red error screen saying something like “this.handleClick is not a function”.



